OL,3,CFirst Minister responds to Starmer
OL,4,Cresignation
OL,6,FResponding to the announcement, Welsh
OL,7,FLabour Interim Leader Ken Skates said:
OL,9,F"Keir brought our party back from
OL,10,Foblivion and delivered one of the
OL,11,Fgreatest victories the Labour Party
OL,12,Fhas seen.
OL,14,FUnder his leadership we've seen an
OL,15,Fincrease to the minimum wage, a boost
OL,16,Fto the state pension and stronger
OL,17,Femployment rights. We also received a
OL,18,Frecord devolution settlement and
OL,19,Fgenerational plans for #14bn for rail
OL,20,Fin Wales.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1782299900
OL,3,CFirst Minister responds to Starmer
OL,4,Cresignation
OL,6,F"He has led the country through
OL,7,Fexceptionally tough times with dignity
OL,8,Fand authenticity, and I want to put on
OL,9,Frecord my deepest thanks to him.
OL,11,FWe now owe it to Keir, and the country
OL,12,Fto come together and ensure that
OL,13,FLabour continues delivering for people
OL,14,Fright across Wales, and the UK."
OL,16,FFirst Minister Rhun ap Iorwerth said:
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1782299900
OL,3,CFirst Minister responds to Starmer
OL,4,Cresignation
OL,6,F"I am disappointed that the Welsh
OL,7,FGovernment's ability to engage with
OL,8,Fthe UK Prime Minister on issues which
OL,9,Fmatter to the people of Wales is being
OL,10,Fhampered by the turmoil in Westminster.
OL,12,F"I wish Sir Keir Starmer well as he
OL,13,Fprepares to leave office. I would like
OL,14,Fto see his successor recognising that
OL,15,FWales needs a new relationship with
OL,16,FWestminster, with a focus on greater
OL,17,Fpowers, fair funding, and respect for
OL,18,Fthe democratic mandate delivered by
OL,19,Fthe people of Wales.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1782299900
OL,3,CFirst Minister responds to Starmer
OL,4,Cresignation
OL,6,F"My government and I will always seek
OL,7,Fa constructive relationship with
OL,8,Fwhoever is in Number 10, but we have
OL,9,Fclear expectations that the respect
OL,10,Fagenda must work both ways."
OL,12,FReform Wales' Leader Dan Thomas MS has
OL,13,Fcalled for a general election
OL,14,Ffollowing the Prime Minister's
OL,15,Fresignation.
OL,17,F"We cannot continue the cycle of Prime
OL,18,FMinisters entering and leaving Number
OL,19,F10 without a clear public mandate.
OL,26,@rD@\O]yD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1782299900
OL,3,CFirst Minister responds to Starmer
OL,4,Cresignation
OL,6,F"More concerning still, Andy Burnham,
OL,7,FStarmer's likely successor, was not
OL,8,Feven an MP when this Labour Government
OL,9,Fwas elected.
OL,11,F"The public must decide who governs
OL,12,Fthe country, not Labour members.
OL,13,FReform demands a general election."
OL,15,FDarren Millar MS, Leader of the Welsh
OL,16,FConservatives, said:
OL,18,F"Sir Keir Starmer may be going, but
OL,19,FLabour's failures remain.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUuD@cO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1782299900
OL,3,CFirst Minister responds to Starmer
OL,4,Cresignation
OL,6,F"The last thing Wales and the rest of
OL,7,Fthe UK needs is another Labour leader
OL,8,Fwho won't stand up to Labour MPs on
OL,9,Fwelfare, energy, defence spending and
OL,10,Faction on the cost of living.
OL,12,F"His decision is a reminder that Kemi
OL,13,FBadenoch is the only leader of a
OL,14,Fpolitical party in the UK with the
OL,15,Fbackbone to make tough decisions and
OL,16,Fget Britain working again."
OL,18,FWelsh Liberal Democrat Spokesperson
OL,19,FDavid Chadwick MP said:
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1782299900
OL,3,CFirst Minister responds to Starmer
OL,4,Cresignation
OL,6,F"Changing the person at the top won't
OL,7,Fchange much unless Labour finally
OL,8,Fconfronts the structural problems that
OL,9,Fcontinue to hold Wales back.
OL,11,F"Despite Labour's catastrophic Senedd
OL,12,Felection results, there is little sign
OL,13,Fthat Westminster Labour's attitude
OL,14,Ftowards Wales has changed.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,438,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1782299900
OL,3,CFirst Minister responds to Starmer
OL,4,Cresignation
OL,6,F"The next Prime Minister must also
OL,7,Flearn a lesson that the last five have
OL,8,Fignored: you cannot sustainably grow
OL,9,Fthe economy without pursuing a closer
OL,10,Frelationship with the EU or
OL,11,Fintroducing a fairer funding formula
OL,12,Ffor Wales that recognises the unique
OL,13,Fneeds of our population.
OL,15,F"Wales needs more than a new Prime
OL,16,FMinister. We need a Westminster
OL,17,Fgovernment that finally takes Wales
OL,18,Fseriously.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
